wikipedia.org/wiki/Pawapuri" title="Pawapuri">Pawapuri</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:47.705%;left:24.569%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Bawangaja" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Bawangaja" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;left:5px;text-align:left"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:left"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bawangaja" title="Bawangaja">Bawangaja</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:38.046%;left:20.147%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Ranakpur" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Ranakpur" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;right:5px;text-align:right"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:right"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranakpur" title="Ranakpur">Ranakpur</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:38.923%;left:40.406%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Khajuraho" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Khajuraho" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;right:5px;text-align:right"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:right"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khajuraho" class="mw-redirect" title="Khajuraho">Khajuraho</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:37.54%;left:50%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Varanasi" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Varanasi" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:5px;left:-3em;text-align:center"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parshvanath_Jain_temple,_Varanasi" title="Parshvanath Jain temple, Varanasi">Varanasi</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:75.818%;left:29.653%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Shravanabelagola" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Shravanabelagola" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;left:5px;text-align:left"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:left"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shravanabelagola" title="Shravanabelagola">Shravanabelagola</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:53.037%;left:58.706%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Udayagiri" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Udayagiri" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;left:5px;text-align:left"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:left"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Udayagiri_and_Khandagiri_Caves" title="Udayagiri and Khandagiri Caves">Udayagiri</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:63.626%;left:23.265%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Kumbhoj" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Kumbhoj" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;left:5px;text-align:left"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:left"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kumbhoj" title="Kumbhoj">Kumbhoj</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:33.179%;left:18.49%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Osian" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Osian" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;right:5px;text-align:right"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:right"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Osian,_Jodhpur" title="Osian, Jodhpur">Osian</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:66.313%;left:27.55%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Pattadakal" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Pattadakal" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:5px;left:-3em;text-align:center"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pattadakal" title="Pattadakal">Pattadakal</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:74.721%;left:28.098%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Halebidu" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Halebidu" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;right:5px;text-align:right"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:right"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Halebidu" class="mw-redirect" title="Halebidu">Halebidu</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:53.764%;left:25.553%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Ellora" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Ellora" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;left:5px;text-align:left"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:left"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ellora" class="mw-redirect" title="Ellora">Ellora</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:64.625%;left:42.443%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Guntur" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Guntur" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;left:5px;text-align:left"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:left"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Undavalli_Caves" title="Undavalli Caves">Guntur</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:60.927%;left:37.616%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Kulpakji" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Kulpakji" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;left:5px;text-align:left"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:left"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kulpakji" title="Kulpakji">Kulpakji</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:84.731%;left:28.919%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Mattancherry" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Mattancherry" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;right:5px;text-align:right"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:right"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mattancherry" title="Mattancherry">Mattancherry</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:77.785%;left:37.719%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Tirumalai" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Tirumalai" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;left:5px;text-align:left"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:left"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tirumalai_(Jain_complex)" title="Tirumalai (Jain complex)">Tirumalai</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:83.217%;left:36.64%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Pudukottai" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Pudukottai" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;bottom:5px;left:-3em;text-align:center"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pudukottai" class="mw-redirect" title="Pudukottai">Pudukottai</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:84.923%;left:34.687%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Madurai" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Madurai" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;left:5px;text-align:left"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:left"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madurai" title="Madurai">Madurai</a></div></div></div><div style="position:absolute;top:89.746%;left:31.998%"><div style="position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0"><img alt="Chitharal" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/8px-Orange_pog.svg.png" decoding="async" title="Chitharal" width="8" height="8" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/12px-Orange_pog.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Orange_pog.svg/16px-Orange_pog.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="64" data-file-height="64" /></div><div style="font-size:90%;line-height:110%;position:absolute;width:6em;top:-0.75em;left:5px;text-align:left"><div style="display:inline;padding:1px;float:left"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chitharal" class="mw-redirect" title="Chitharal">Chitharal</a></div></div></div></div><div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:India_location_map.svg" title="File:India location map.svg"> </a></div>Major pilgrimage and temple sites in Jainism.</div></div></div>
<p>A Jain temple, a <i>Derasar</i> or <i>Basadi</i>, is a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Place_of_worship" title="Place of worship">place of worship</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBabb199666_273-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTEBabb199666-273">&#91;264&#93;</a></sup> Temples contain <i>tirthankara</i> images, some fixed, others moveable.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBabb199666_273-1" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTEBabb199666-273">&#91;264&#93;</a></sup> These are stationed in the inner sanctum, one of the two sacred zones, the other being the main hall.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBabb199666_273-2" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTEBabb199666-273">&#91;264&#93;</a></sup> One of the images is marked as the <i>moolnayak</i> (primary deity).<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBabb199668_274-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTEBabb199668-274">&#91;265&#93;</a></sup> A <i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manastambha" title="Manastambha">manastambha</a></i> (column of honor) is a pillar that is often constructed in front of Jain temples.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTESettar1989195_275-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTESettar1989195-275">&#91;266&#93;</a></sup> Temple construction is considered a meritorious act.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTESangave2001188_276-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTESangave2001188-276">&#91;267&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Ancient Jain monuments include the Udaigiri Hills near Bhelsa (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vidisha" title="Vidisha">Vidisha</a>) in Madhya Pradesh, the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ellora_Caves" title="Ellora Caves">Ellora</a> in Maharashtra, the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palitana_temples" title="Palitana temples">Palitana temples</a> in Gujarat, and the Jain temples at Dilwara Temples near <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Abu" title="Mount Abu">Mount Abu</a>, Rajasthan.<sup id="cite_ref-277" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-277">&#91;268&#93;</a></sup> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranakpur_Jain_temple" title="Ranakpur Jain temple">Chaumukha temple</a> in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranakpur" title="Ranakpur">Ranakpur</a> is considered one of the most beautiful Jain temples and is famous for its detailed carvings.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTESehdev_Kumar2001106_278-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTESehdev_Kumar2001106-278">&#91;269&#93;</a></sup> According to Jain texts, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shikharji" title="Shikharji">Shikharji</a> is the place where twenty of the twenty-four Jain <i>Tīrthaṅkaras</i> along with many other monks attained <i>moksha</i> (died without being reborn, with their soul in <i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siddhashila" title="Siddhashila">Siddhashila</a></i>). The Shikharji site in northeastern <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jharkhand" title="Jharkhand">Jharkhand</a> is therefore a revered pilgrimage site.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTECort2010130–133_279-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTECort2010130–133-279">&#91;270&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-281" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-281">&#91;j&#93;</a></sup> The Palitana temples are the holiest shrine for the Śvētāmbara Murtipujaka sect.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBerger2010352_282-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTEBerger2010352-282">&#91;272&#93;</a></sup> Along with Shikharji the two sites are considered the holiest of all pilgrimage sites by the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jain_community" class="mw-redirect" title="Jain community">Jain community</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-283" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-283">&#91;273&#93;</a></sup> The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jain_complex,_Khajuraho" class="mw-redirect" title="Jain complex, Khajuraho">Jain complex, Khajuraho</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pattadakal#Jain_Temple" title="Pattadakal">Jain Narayana temple</a> are part of a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UNESCO" title="UNESCO">UNESCO</a> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Heritage_Site" title="World Heritage Site">World Heritage Site</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-284" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-284">&#91;274&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-285" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-285">&#91;275&#93;</a></sup> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shravanabelagola" title="Shravanabelagola">Shravanabelagola</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saavira_Kambada_Basadi" title="Saavira Kambada Basadi">Saavira Kambada Basadi</a> or <i>1000 pillars</i> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brahma_Jinalaya" class="mw-redirect" title="Brahma Jinalaya">Brahma Jinalaya</a> are important Jain centers in Karnataka.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEButaliaSmall2004367_286-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTEButaliaSmall2004367-286">&#91;276&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEFergusson1876271_287-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTEFergusson1876271-287">&#91;277&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEPandya201417_288-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTEPandya201417-288">&#91;278&#93;</a></sup> In and around <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madurai" title="Madurai">Madurai</a>, there are 26 caves, 200 stone beds, 60 inscriptions, and over 100 sculptures. <sup id="cite_ref-289" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-289">&#91;279&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>The 2nd–1st century BCE Udayagiri and Khandagiri Caves are rich with carvings of <i>tirthanakars</i> and deities with inscriptions including the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hathigumpha_inscription" title="Hathigumpha inscription">Elephant Cave inscription</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-290" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-290">&#91;280&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEUpinder_Singh2016460_291-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTEUpinder_Singh2016460-291">&#91;281&#93;</a></sup> Jain cave temples at <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Badami_cave_temples" title="Badami cave temples">Badami</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mangi-Tungi" title="Mangi-Tungi">Mangi-Tungi</a> and the Ellora Caves are considered important.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEOwen2012a50_292-0" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-FOOTNOTEOwen2012a50-292">&#91;282&#93;</a></sup> The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sittanavasal_Cave" title="Sittanavasal Cave">Sittanavasal Cave</a> temple is a fine example of Jain art with an early cave shelter, and a medieval rock-cut temple with excellent fresco paintings comparable to Ajantha. Inside are seventeen stone beds with 2nd century BCE <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tamil-Brahmi" title="Tamil-Brahmi">Tamil-Brahmi</a> inscriptions.<sup id="cite_ref-293" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-293">&#91;283&#93;</a></sup> The 8th century <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kalugumalai_Jain_Beds" title="Kalugumalai Jain Beds">Kazhugumalai temple</a> marks the revival of Jainism in South India.<sup id="cite_ref-294" class="reference"><a href="Jainism#cite_note-294">&#91;284&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<ul class="gallery mw-gallery-packed">
	<li class="gallerycaption">Jain temples of varied styles in India and abroad</li>
